Aaron Davey (born 10 June 1983) is a professional Australian rules football player of Indigenous Australian heritage. He played for the Melbourne Football Club in the Australian Football League (AFL) until he retired from the club at the end of the 2013 season.
Davey finished runner-up to the AFL Rising Star in 2004.

people.name: Steve von Bergen
people.aboutText: Steve von Bergen (born 10 June 1983) is a Swiss professional footballer who plays as defender for Young Boys. He played for FC Zürich for two full seasons, winning the Swiss Super League in both campaigns and then moved to Hertha BSC, playing there for three years. He managed to establish himself as a regular on the Switzerland national football team, earning over 40 caps since his debut in 2006 and playing at two World Cups.

people.name: Johanna Kedzierski
people.aboutText:
Johanna Kedzierski (born 10 June 1984 in Wejherowo, Poland) is a German sprinter who specializes in the 200 metres.
At the 2007 World Championships in Athletics – Women's 4 × 100 metres relay she finished seventh together with teammates Katja Wakan, Cathleen Tschirch and Verena Sailer. She won a relay silver medal at the 2005 European Athletics Junior Championships.

people.name: Dirk Van Tichelt
people.aboutText:
Dirk Van Tichelt (born 10 June 1984) is a Belgian judoka.
His biggest achievement was his European title in Lisbon. In the same year, at the Beijing Olympics he came fifth after losing in the first round to gold-medallist Elnur Mammadli and later losing in the bronze medal match to Rasul Boqiev.

people.name: Richard Chambers
people.aboutText: Richard Scott Chambers (born 10 June 1985) is a British rower, and is the brother of fellow rower Peter Chambers.

people.name: Gert Dorbek
people.aboutText: Kaia Kanepi (pronunciation: KY-ah KAH-nep-i; IPA: [ˈkɑiɑ ˈkɑnepi]; born 10 June 1985) is an Estonian tennis player. She achieved her career-high ranking of World No. 15 in August 2012 and holds many firsts for Estonia.

people.name: Kaia Kanepi
people.aboutText: Gert Dorbek (born 10 June 1985) is an Estonian professional basketball player. He is currently playing for Tartu Ülikool/Rock at the guard position. He is a nephew of Aivar Kuusmaa, former Panathinaikos B.C. shooter and Soviet champion.

people.name: Kristina Lundberg
people.aboutText: Kristina Anna Maria Lundberg (born June 10, 1985 in Husum, Sweden) is a Swedish ice hockey player. She won a silver medal at the 2006 Winter Olympics.

people.name: Andy Schleck
people.aboutText: Andy Raymond Schleck (pronounced [ɑndi ʀɑɪ̯mond ʃlæk]; born 10 June 1985) is a Luxembourg former professional road bicycle racer. He won the 2010 Tour de France, being awarded it retroactively in February 2012 after Alberto Contador's hearing at the Court of Arbitration for Sport. He has also been the runner-up at the Tour twice; in 2009 and 2011.

people.name: Vasilis Torosidis
people.aboutText:
Vasileios "Vasilis" Torosidis (Greek: Βασίλης Τοροσίδης; born 10 June 1985) is a Greek footballer who currently plays for Italian Serie A club Roma and the Greek national team.
The 30-year-old is hugely versatile and regularly plays in different positions both for his club and country. Boasting great energy, a willingness to get forward and strong heading ability, the Greek star is a manager's dream as he can fill in all over the park.

people.name: Kreesha Turner
people.aboutText: Kreesha Turner (born June 10, 1985) is a Canadian/Jamaican recording artist and songwriter. Born in Edmonton, Alberta, Canada. Raised in both Canada and Jamaica, she began her musical career after a successful audition with Virgin Records.

people.name: Nikki Jayne
people.aboutText: Nikki Jayne (born June 10, 1985) is the stage name of a British pornographic actress.

people.name: Marco Andreolli

people.name: Zara Dampney
people.aboutText: Zara Dampney (born 10 June 1986) is a British beach volleyball player, and former indoor volleyball player. She has been chosen as one of the two players to take the home nation qualification spot at the 2012 Summer Olympics.

people.name: Hajime Hosogai
people.aboutText: Keith Harkin (born (1986-06-10)10 June 1986 in Derry, Northern Ireland) is a singer and songwriter.

Zimmerman was born in Albuquerque, New Mexico to Kat and Harry Zimmerman, a Los Angeles-based actor; his parents are divorced and he lives with his mother.

people.name: Lyssa Chapman
people.aboutText: Lyssa Rae Chapman (born June 10, 1987), more commonly known as "Baby Lyssa", is an American bail bondswoman and bounty hunter, most noted for her role on A&E TV's Dog the Bounty Hunter, in which she, along with her father Duane "Dog" Chapman and various friends and family, track down and capture wanted fugitives.

people.name: Martin Harnik

people.name: Patrik Lindberg
people.aboutText: Patrik Lindberg (born June 10, 1988), known by the pseudonym f0rest, is a Swedish Counter-Strike and Counter-Strike: Global Offensive player. Having played competitively since 2005, Lindberg, has widely gained a reputation within the esports scene as one of the best-performing Counter-Strike players in the world. Lindberg is best known for his four years of tenure on the Fnatic roster, which he helped bring to prominence as the dominant team of 2009, during which year the team broke the record for the highest-earning team in Counter-Strike history.

people.name: Melanie Müller

Melanie "Melli" Müller (born 10 June 1988) is a German television personality, model and former pornographic actress.

people.name: Alexandra Stan

She subsequently released her debut recording "Lollipop (Param Pam Pam)" in late 2009.

people.name: Ryuya Wakaba

people.name: Valeen Montenegro

people.aboutText: Valeen Montenegro Vicente (born 10 June 1990), commonly known for her stage name as Valeen Montenegro, is a Filipina actress.

people.aboutText: Julian de la Celle (born June 10, 1996 in Los Angeles, California) is an American actor. He played Daniel Meade, Jr. (affectionately known as DJ), Alexis Meade's son, in ABC's Ugly Betty.

people.aboutText: Annefleur Kalvenhaar (10 June 1994 – 23 August 2014) was a Dutch cyclist and mountain biker. She won the U23 European Cyclo-cross Championships in 2013. She began her career at the age of 13.

Kristjan Ilves (born (1996-06-10)June 10, 1996 in Tartu) is an Estonian Nordic combined skier.
Ilves competed at the 2014 Winter Olympics for Estonia. He placed 41st in the normal hill Nordic combined event, and 34th in the large hill event.
